LIMBUS (
Fig. 58C
). Margin with short, blunt-angled yet pointed lobes, smooth except for one ridge running into each lobe.

FIRST PAIR OF LEGS (
Fig. 58E–G
). Prefemoral lobes rounded-triangular in ventral view. One to two coxosternal setae (
CXS
) close to lateral margin of coxosternum, well separated from prefemoral lobes. Prefemora with two mesapical setae (
APS
) and a few lateral setae (
LPS
).

